    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-20T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-20T10:00:00-05:00" n="524"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 863.852/12</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PFC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-20T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 22, 3 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1773. Referring to Department’s telegram 791, July 14, 1915, and subsequent
                        correspondence.<note n="1" xml:id="d524fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    Austro-Americana Steamship Co. requests <pb facs="0530" n="446" xml:id="pg_446"
                    /> transmission of following telegram to their agents, Phelps Bros., 17 Battery
                    Place, New York: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>You have authority after consulting with Buenos Aires to sell to neutral
                            buyers our <hi rend="italic">Dora, Erny, Lucia</hi>, minimum $160; <hi
                                rend="italic">Clara, Ida, Teresa</hi>, $150 per ton dead weight; <hi
                                rend="italic">Anna</hi> best possible; cash payment through Holland
                            less one-fifth to remain at Buenos Aires’ disposal. Buyers must,
                            however, guarantee either to keep vessels in port during present war or
                            run them only between present neutral American ports giving at the same
                            time substantial guarantee to that effect. Eventual expenses of putting
                            vessels on highest Lloyd register class to be at our charge for same.
                            Please communicate us direct reply soonest possible.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
